1
00:00:42,676 --> 00:00:44,670
Wielding a sword is no game.

2
00:00:46,170 --> 00:00:49,083
If you make even a single mistake, you could get hurt.

3
00:00:50,130 --> 00:00:51,846
You must learn to control your strength.

4
00:00:53,720 --> 00:00:57,144
Then teach me how to control it.

5
00:00:57,980 --> 00:00:59,360
Or is it that you simply don't know how to teach?

6
00:01:00,806 --> 00:01:02,363
You must listen to me.

7
00:01:03,190 --> 00:01:06,196
Am I not standing right here, ready for your lesson?

8
00:01:13,020 --> 00:01:13,704
Raise your sword.

9
00:01:27,720 --> 00:01:29,833
If you had held me like this from the very beginning,

10
00:01:30,620 --> 00:01:32,196
I would have mastered this long ago.

11
00:01:36,010 --> 00:01:37,027
Focus.

12
00:01:38,200 --> 00:01:39,470
I am focusing.

13
00:01:40,018 --> 00:01:42,010
Or is it you who is losing focus?

14
00:01:53,360 --> 00:01:54,609
You are holding me so tightly.

15
00:01:54,940 --> 00:01:56,301
Can you be a bit gentler?

16
00:01:57,820 --> 00:01:58,953
If I do not hold tight,

17
00:01:59,900 --> 00:02:01,316
the sword will fly out of your hand.

18
00:02:03,560 --> 00:02:05,655
Or are you afraid that I am the one who will slip through your hand?

19
00:02:16,510 --> 00:02:19,907
The most important thing in sword fighting is not physical strength.

20
00:02:20,203 --> 00:02:21,290
It is the mind.

21
00:02:24,140 --> 00:02:25,846
You must keep your concentration steady

22
00:02:26,840 --> 00:02:28,055
and keep your eyes fixed on your opponent.

23
00:02:45,710 --> 00:02:46,750
Like this?

24
00:02:47,630 --> 00:02:49,101
Does this count as concentration?

25
00:02:50,930 --> 00:02:53,864
If you are still talking, it does not count as concentration.

26
00:02:55,940 --> 00:02:58,369
In that case, I shall say no more.

27
00:03:12,250 --> 00:03:13,969
Didn't you tell me not to be shaken?

28
00:03:14,730 --> 00:03:15,852
Why are you backing away, then?

29
00:03:18,240 --> 00:03:19,981
I still have it under control.

30
00:03:20,440 --> 00:03:21,723
Then do not back away.

31
00:03:24,363 --> 00:03:26,360
Is this what is breaking your focus?

32
00:03:27,240 --> 00:03:28,166
Or is it me?

33
00:03:32,580 --> 00:03:34,473
If you keep playing around like this,

34
00:03:35,160 --> 00:03:36,683
I will not be able to teach you.

35
00:03:37,990 --> 00:03:39,138
In that case,

36
00:03:40,190 --> 00:03:41,870
bring me under your control,

37
00:03:42,730 --> 00:03:44,049
my bodyguard.

38
00:04:06,890 --> 00:04:07,956
I do not want to eat.

39
00:04:09,290 --> 00:04:11,089
But you haven't eaten anything all day.

40
00:04:13,530 --> 00:04:15,243
The food here is not quite to my liking.

41
00:04:16,630 --> 00:04:19,618
So that is why you are so thin.

42
00:04:24,500 --> 00:04:26,233
And how do you know I am thin?

43
00:04:27,390 --> 00:04:28,467
Have you ever touched me?

44
00:04:33,064 --> 00:04:35,286
What would you like to eat? I shall prepare it for you.

45
00:04:39,240 --> 00:04:40,369
You know how to cook?

46
00:04:59,710 --> 00:05:03,083
I thought only noblewomen knew how to prepare meals.

47
00:05:08,830 --> 00:05:12,972
My father fell ill, so I had to cook for him.

48
00:05:17,840 --> 00:05:20,640
Ah, so you have been practicing for a long time

49
00:05:30,870 --> 00:05:32,166
Is there nothing spicy at all?

50
00:05:33,570 --> 00:05:34,658
But you do not eat spicy food.

51
00:05:38,650 --> 00:05:40,246
So what kind of curry is this?

52
00:05:41,470 --> 00:05:42,424
Thai jungle curry

53
00:05:44,090 --> 00:05:45,064
Is it spicy?

54
00:05:45,850 --> 00:05:46,486
Very spicy

55
00:05:49,040 --> 00:05:51,107
Then, I guess I wouldn’t like it.

56
00:05:55,040 --> 00:05:56,203
You still remember?

57
00:05:58,490 --> 00:06:01,821
I remember everything about you.

58
00:06:17,260 --> 00:06:18,418
Does it suit your palate?

59
00:06:23,300 --> 00:06:24,769
If it is too salty, I can make...

60
00:06:24,787 --> 00:06:25,575
It's delicious.

61
00:06:30,740 --> 00:06:31,667
Incredibly delicious.

62
00:06:33,940 --> 00:06:37,156
Now that I've tasted it, I don't want to stop.

63
00:06:48,040 --> 00:06:49,298
I am glad to hear that.

64
00:06:53,630 --> 00:06:56,590
Or did you secretly put something in it?

65
00:06:58,800 --> 00:06:59,649
Put what in it?

66
00:07:02,610 --> 00:07:11,421
Why is it that the more I taste it, the more I find myself wanting to look at the cook's face?

67
00:07:19,670 --> 00:07:21,101
I am only speaking the truth.

68
00:07:24,110 --> 00:07:25,261
Have you tasted it yourself yet?

69
00:07:33,320 --> 00:07:34,283
If not, try some.

70
00:08:16,820 --> 00:08:22,523
My bodyguard is indeed quite obedient.

71
00:08:27,810 --> 00:08:31,950
The food you make is just like you.

72
00:08:36,440 --> 00:08:37,261
How so?

73
00:08:44,090 --> 00:08:45,446
Warm and...

74
00:08:47,310 --> 00:08:49,507
making me want to taste it all the time.

75
00:09:06,740 --> 00:09:07,655
It is getting late.

76
00:09:08,950 --> 00:09:10,110
I must head back now.

77
00:09:11,920 --> 00:09:12,781
Not just yet.

78
00:09:19,150 --> 00:09:21,200
I have an important matter I need your help with.
